00:53:57.017 --> 00:54:01.121 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Belarus is an Eastern European nation
that borders Russia.

00:54:02.222 --> 00:54:04.224 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s known as

00:54:04.224 --> 00:54:08.228 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the “blue-eyed” country
because it is dotted

00:54:08.228 --> 00:54:11.364 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with more than 10,000 lakes.

00:54:11.364 --> 00:54:16.403 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Some of Europe’s
most ancient trees, as well as

00:54:16.403 --> 00:54:19.339 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
its largest mammal
—the European bison—

00:54:19.339 --> 00:54:21.141 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
can be found here.

00:54:22.108 --> 00:54:24.511 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Castles, some dating

00:54:24.511 --> 00:54:28.181 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
from the 16th century, are popular sites.

00:54:28.181 --> 00:54:31.985 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is Nesvizh Castle.

00:54:31.985 --> 00:54:36.323 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
If you look up at the ceiling of its chapel,
you’ll see Jehovah’s name

00:54:36.323 --> 00:54:40.093 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in the form of the Tetragrammaton.

00:54:40.093 --> 00:54:44.097 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When Belarus was part of the Soviet Union,

00:54:44.097 --> 00:54:48.835 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah’s Witnesses
faced strong government opposition.

00:54:49.569 --> 00:54:54.040 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Some of our brothers
were exiled to far-away Siberia.

00:54:54.040 --> 00:54:58.011 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Today, more than 6,000 publishers

00:54:58.011 --> 00:55:02.449 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in 84 congregations
boldly declare the good news

00:55:02.449 --> 00:55:05.085 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in Belarus.

00:55:05.085 --> 00:55:07.821 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There is a zealous pioneer spirit here.

00:55:07.821 --> 00:55:11.358 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Twenty percent of the publishers

00:55:11.358 --> 00:55:13.360 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
are in full-time service.

00:55:14.494 --> 00:55:17.530 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is how our brothers share the good news

00:55:17.530 --> 00:55:18.698 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in the city of Brest.

00:55:18.698 --> 00:55:21.001 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
